Steel Technologies Inc said itagreed to form a 50-50 joint venture with &lt;Mitsui and Co Ltd>to make steel products.    The venture, called Mi-Tech Steel Inc, will be set up toserve Japanese and domestic automobile and appliance partsmakers in the U.S.    A plant will be located near Murfreesboro, Tenn., andproduction is expected to begin in the fall 1987, the companysaid. Reuter&#3;